BRITS – The Brits Magistrate’s Court on Thursday, sentenced a man was to a year imprisonment or an R6,000 fine for stabbing another man. Mpho Thobejane pleaded guilty for stabbing Piet Aphane in the neck in Oukasie near Brits on September 9. “The woman I am staying with is the mother to Aphane’s children. He verbally abused me, accused me of not taking good care of his children. I got angry and I stabbed him,” he told the court. He was sentenced to 12 months imprisonment or to pay an R6,000 fine suspended for five. He was charged with assault with the intention to inflict grievous bodily harm. African News Agency